      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "D MAC NZ (7) is a lightly raced but progressive colt who won his two Perth starts as a juvenile, highlighted by the Group 1 Golden Slipper when last seen in September. Cops a wide draw for his return but may have developed further with maturity. WISHING BELLE (4) was a beaten favourite first up but she drew very wide and was only was a neck away in second. Had put together a string of wins here last campaign including the G1 Westbred Classic. May strip fitter than the top pick with a run under her belt and draws inside him. Big chance. PROPOSITION JOE NZ (6) suffered his first defeat when he raced parked from this barrier but stuck on for a solid second at Pinjarra last time. First try here but he has plenty of upside. CRUNCHNSIP (2) draws well and is in the mix for the exotics after turning in a better effort last start to finish third at this venue. Include from the low draw.",
